    <apex:define name="_content">
        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span12">
                <div class="well" style="border: 2px solid #049cdb;">
                    <h1>SDO Chatter Charades</h1>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span6">
                <p><span class="label label-info">Chatter Charades</span> is a two part component to let you quickly post as anyone in chatter, and build a complex, natural conversation in half the time.</p>
                <p>First component is a sidebar element that is context sensitive, letting you post to whatever object you&apos;re on, or otherwise post directly to any user/group, AS any user. 
                   This definitely includes Content and Links.</p>
                <p>Second component is a subtle * link on every post, that lets you comment on the fly, again as any user.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <br/>
        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span6">
                <p>Add <span class="label label-info">Chatter Charades</span> sidebar component to your homepage layout.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <br/>
        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span6">
                <p><span class="label label-warning">NOTES</span> - Do not use while in Developer Mode. Evil things fly out of your computer, and the tool generally fails.
                   You *cannot* post to a group as a user that is not a member of that group.
                   Since you can&apos;t have a sidebar on a group/user page(yet?), you need to utilize the sidebar component&apos;s tabs for User/Group to post to those objects. 
                   The *only* page you can reliably post comments to threads in groups is in your homepage feed. This means you&apos;ll need to make yourself a member of that group temporarily, then return to the home page to use the comment feature in order to build your conversations.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <br/>
        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span12">
                <img src="/resource/charadesImg"/>
            </div>
        </div>             
